## Chapter 48 Live-Data Prototype Technique

* Sometimes in discovery you need to validate an idea through use, investigation or analysis of production data.
* A live data prototype is a very limited implementation. It is substantially smaller than the eventual product, and the bar is dramatically lower in terms of quality, performance and functionality.
* The key is to be able to send some limited amount of traffic, and to collect analytics on how this live-data prototype is being used.
